 luke ben spoke gently going to find that many of the truth we clingto depend greatly on our point of view 
 luke turned unresponsive he wanted to hold onto his fury to guard it like atreasure it was all he had he would not let it be stolen from him as everything elsehad been stolen but already he felt it slipping softened by compassionatetouch 
 i blame you for being angry ben coaxed if i was wrong in what i certainly have been for the first time you see what happened to yourfather was my fault 
 luke looked up with sudden acute interest never heard this and wasrapidly losing his anger to fascination and knowledge was an addictivedrug and the more he had the more he wanted 
 as he sat on his stump increasingly mesmerized artoo pedaled over silent justto offer a comforting presence 
 when i first encountered your father ben continued he was already a greatpilot but what amazed me was how strongly the force was with him i took itupon myself to train anakin in the ways of the jedi my mistake was thinking icould be as good a teacher as yoda i was not such was my foolish pride theemperor sensed power and he lured him to the dark side he pausedsadly and looked directly into eyes as if he were asking for the my pride had terrible consequences for the galaxy 
 luke was entranced that hubris could have caused his fallwas horrible horrible because of what his father had needlessly become horriblebecause perfect even a perfect jedi horrible because the darkside could strike so close to him could turn such right so wring darth vader mustyet have a spark of anakin skywalker deep inside there is still good in him hedeclared 
 ben shook his head remorsefully i also thought he could be turned back to thegood side it be done he is more machine now than andevil 
 luke sensed the underlying meaning in statement he heard the wordsas a command he shook his head back at the vision i kill my own father 
